reviews.review_text: Poor sound quality! I started listening to this show but the recording is awful and wouldnt subject my coworkers to cruel and unusual punishment =). I'm sure the performance is fine, its '73 after all. We need a better source.

sbd? anyone? rating for sound quality and not performance, per se. horrid audience. A fine example of why they eventually set up taper's sections. This Playin'>Uncle John's>Playin' is one of my favorites ever, and was played on Dead Hour (along with several other tunes) years ago. Someone please post a SBD for our listening enjoyment. It's a shame that P>UJB>P didn't get on the Dick's Picks that featured the previous and following nights - it's that good, IMHO.
